author: Erinda P.
text: Thank you DW for sharing this. I think this documentary portrays very well the complexity of the problem we stand before. Our energy demands are only  increasing but our sense of awareness to the repercussions of such needs are also increasing. This means we will stand before many difficult decisions now and in the future, and need to carefully weigh out the consequences. Fast acting is not possible, yet it is highly necessary as our carbon budget for a 1.5C scenario is practically depleted already. A long-term planning vision and political framework that enables it is highly needed, but extremely complex in a political landscape that is becoming more and more nationalistic. So, what can we do? I don't have the answer but it is clear that one nation alone will not solve the issue. We need to work together and find common solutions which are not driven by capitalist objectives. \nIn addition to my philosophical rant (thanks for baring with me) I would like to point out that also nuclear power has issues related to GHG emissions, besides the safety hazards.
